attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Linux botnet or Command and Control (C2) agent, specifically identifying itself in metadata as the 'NexusCorp C2 Persistence Daemon'. It exhibits aggressive persistence behaviors across multiple Linux initialization systems, including modifying /etc/inittab for respawn, /etc/rc.local for startup execution, crontab for reboot persistence, and installing a custom systemd service at /etc/systemd/system/persist.service. The binary copies itself to '/usr/local/bin/sysd' to masquerade as a system daemon. It contains a large state machine for processing remote commands, network socket logic for C2 communication, and functions to execute shell commands via /bin/sh.
